block content

  +state('Wyoming', '/assets/images/flag-wyoming.svg', 'The Equality State', 'July 10, 1890')

  .intro
    p In 1916, the Wyoming Daughters of the American Revolution (DAR) organized a contest to design the state flag.
    p The winning design, featuring the state seal upon a bison, was submitted by Verna Keays, a local artist. Dr. Grace Raymond Hebard, state regent for DAR, suggested the bison be flipped so it faced the hoist.
    p With this change, the flag was offically adopted January 31, 1917.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p An outside border of red surrounds another border of white.
      p Inside the borders, a field of blue with a white silhouetted bison placed at the center.
      p Upon the bison’s shoulder is the state seal in blue and white.
    .visual.flag
      img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-bison.svg')
          h4 bison
          p state mammal, regional fauna
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-seal.svg')
          h4 seal
          p western custom of branding
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-equal-rights.svg')
          h4 woman
          p equality, women’s suffrage
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-pillars.svg')
          h4 pillars
          p livestock, mining, agriculture, oil industries
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-cowboy.svg')
          h4 cowboy
          p livestock, rodeo
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-miner.svg')
          h4 miner
          p mining industry
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-eagle.svg')
          h4 eagle
          p freedom, the United States
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-dates.svg')
          h4 1869 & 1890
          p year Wyoming Territory established women’s suffrage, year of Wyoming’s statehood
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-icon-star.svg')
          h4 star
          p Wyoming as the 44th state

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p The Wyoming flag uses the same red, white, and blue as the U.S. national flag.
      hr
      small According to Keays, the blue represented fidelity, justice, and virility. The red symbolized the Native peoples and the blood spilled in war. The white represented purity and uprightness.
    .visual.colors.primary
      include includes/color-us-blue
      include includes/color-us-red
      include includes/color-white

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p The Wyoming flag has a proportion of 7:10.
      p The red border is 1/20 and the white border is 1/40 the length of the fly.
      p The bison is 1/2 the length of the blue field and the state seal is 1/5 the length of the fly.
      p If resized, it must maintain these proportions.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-wyoming-dimensions.svg')

